INSERT INTO `es_pt_model_errorcode` VALUES (1,1,'SC-F6330','0000','CPU becomes out of control','Main Board','The RAM could have failed','Replace the Main Board'),(2,1,'SC-F6330','0001','NMI Error','Main Board','Main Board Electric Circuit failure','1. Check if the product recovers by turning the power OFF/ON.<br>2. Replace the Main Board.'),(3,1,'SC-F6330','1101','CR Life End Error','Ink Tube','The CR Scanning Path Counter has reached the end of the service life (=Ink Tube life end).','Replace the Ink Tube (P. 278), and reset the life counter'),(4,1,'SC-F6330','1125','CR Home Position Detection Error','1. CR HP Sensor<br>2. Shield Plate of CR Unit<br>3. CR Scale<br>4. Paper jam inside the printer<br>5. CR Lock<br>6. CR Encoder','The CR HP Sensor cannot detect the CR Unit. Or, since the home contact position cannot be detected, the CR home position cannot be set','1. Remove the jammed paper.<br>2. Check for CR HP Sensor failure (if the Shield Plate reacts to the sensor).<br>3. Check for CR Unit Shield Plate failure, scratches or contamination on the CR Scale. If the CR Scale is contaminated, clean it with ethanol.<br>4. Check CR Lock release.<br>5. Replace the CR Scale.<br>6. Check the reading state of the CR Encoder. If reading (from the Service Program) cannot be performed, reinstall the CR Encoder.<br>7. If there is any abnormality in the CR Encoder, replace it.<br>8. Replace the CR HP Sensor.<br>9. Replace the CR Lock (Pump Cap Unit).'),(5,1,'SC-F6330','1138','CR Motor Overcurrent Error','1. Maintenance Cover Sensor<br>2. CR Encoder<br>3. CR Motor','1. There is an abnormality in the Maintenance Cover Sensor connection.<br>2. Maintenance Cover Sensor failure<br>3. There is an abnormality in the CR Motor or CR Encoder connection.<br>4. The number of times of the detection of overcurrent flowing to the CR Motor has reached the specified value.','1. Check the following connections again for an abnormality such as a connector disconnection or a broken cable. If an abnormality is found, reconnect it.<br>2. Check the reading state of the CR Encoder. If reading (from the Service Program) cannot be performed, reinstall the CR Encoder.<br>3. Replace the Maintenance Cover Sensor.<br>4. Replace the CR Encoder.<br>5. Replace the CR Motor.'),(6,1,'SC-F6330','1139','CR Motor Oscillation Error','1. Main Board (CR Motor Driver)<br>2. CR Motor','The number of oscillations exceeds the specified value. Or, the control terminal (Vre terminal) of the CR Motor Driver was short-circuited.','1. Check for damage on the CR Motor Driver of the<br>Main Board.<br>2. Check for foreign objects near the CR Motor Driver.<br>If a foreign object is found, remove it.<br>3. If the product does not recover, replace the Main<br>Board.<br>4. Replace the CR Motor.'),(7,1,'SC-F6330','113A','CR Motor Overload Error','1. CR Unit<br>2. CR Encoder<br>3. CR Motor<br>4. CR Encoder<br>5. CR Motor','The CR Motor did not operate normally due to some load and an overcurrent higher than the specified value was detected. The CR Motor rotation speed is not attained or is not detected correctly.','1. Check the obstacle in the CR moving range.<br>2. Check the CR Unit state.<br>3. Check the following connections for an abnormality such as a connector disconnection or a broken cable. If an abnormality is found, reconnect it.<br>4. Check the reading state of the CR Encoder. If reading (from the Service Program) cannot be performed, reinstall the CR Encoder.<br>5. Lubrication to the CR Oil Pad.<br>6. Install the CR Unit correctly.<br>7. Replace the CR Encoder.<br>8. Replace the CR Motor.'),(8,1,'SC-F6330','113B','CR Motor Over Speed Error','1. CR Scale<br>2. CR Encoder<br>3. Sub Board<br>4. Main Board','The CR Motor was detected to be operating at a speed faster than the specified speed when decelerating.','1. Is the CR Scale contaminated? If the CR Scale is contaminated, clean it.<br>2. Check the reading state of the CR Encoder. If reading (from the Service Program) cannot be performed, reinstall the CR Encoder.<br>3. Replace the CR Encoder.<br>4. Replace the Sub Board.<br>5. Replace the Main Board.'),(9,1,'SC-F6330','113C','The number of occurrences of reversing the CR Motor has reached a predetermined limit.','1. CR Belt tension<br>2. CR Encoder<br>3. CR Motor','CR Motor Reversing Error','1. Check the reading state of the CR Encoder. If reading (from the Service Program) cannot be performed, reinstall the CR Encoder.<br>2. Check the following connections for an abnormality such as a connector disconnection or a broken cable. If an abnormality is found, reconnect it.<br>3. Replace the CR Encoder.<br>4. Check the CR Belt state.<br>5. Replace the CR Motor.'),(10,1,'SC-F6330','113D','CR Motor Driving Time-Out Error','Main Board','Abnormally-long driving duration of the CR Motor was detected.','Replace the Main Board'),(11,1,'SC-F6330','113E','CR Motor Velocity Deviation Error','1. CR Scale<br>2. CR Encoder<br>3. Sub Board<br>4. Main Board','The CR Motor was driven at a speed abnormally faster than a predetermined one during acceleration or deceleration','1. Check for CR Scale contamination and if it is found to be contaminated, clean it.<br>2. Check the reading state of the CR Encoder. If reading (from the Service Program) cannot be performed, reinstall the CR Encoder.<br>3. Replace the CR Encoder.<br>4. Replace the Sub Board.<br>5. Replace the Main Board.'),(12,1,'SC-F6330','113F','CR Motor Lock Error','1. CR Belt tension<br>2. CR Encoder<br>3. CR Motor','The CR Motor was driven at a speed abnormally slower than a predetermined one during operation. Or, the waveform is not detected when the CR Motor is driving.','1. Check the CR Belt state.<br>2. Check the following connections for an abnormality such as a connector disconnection or a broken cable. If an abnormality is found, reconnect it.<br>3. Check the reading state of the CR Encoder. If reading (from the Service Program) cannot be performed, reinstall the CR Encoder.<br>4. Replace the CR Encoder.<br>5. Replace the CR Motor.'),(13,1,'SC-F6330','1229','PF Motor Oscillation Error','1. Main Board (PF Motor Driver)<br>2. PF Motor','The number of oscillations exceeds the specified value. Or, the control terminal (Vre terminal) of the PF Motor Driver was short-circuited.','1. Check the Main Board state.<br>2. Is the Main Board damaged? If the product does not recover, replace the Main Board.<br>3. Replace the PF Motor.'),(14,1,'SC-F6330','122A','PF Motor Overload Error','1. PF Unit<br>2. PF Encoder<br>3. PF Motor<br>4. Main Board','Overcurrent to the PF Motor was detected. The PF Motor rotation speed is not attained or is not detected correctly','1. Check the obstacle in the PF moving range.<br>2. Is the PF Unit installed correctly?<br>3. Check the following connections for an abnormality such as a connector disconnection or a broken cable. If an abnormality is found, reconnect it.<br>4. Check the reading state of the PF Encoder. If reading (from the Service Program) cannot be performed, reinstall the PF Encoder.<br>5. Replace the PF Encoder.<br>6. Is there a foreign object in the driving section of the PF Motor?<br>7. Replace the PF Motor.<br>8.Replace the Main Board.'),(15,1,'SC-F6330','122B','PF Motor Over Speed Error','1. PF Scale<br>2. PF Encoder<br>3. Sub-B Board<br>4. Main Board','The PF Motor was detected to be operating at a speed faster than the specified speed when decelerating.','1 .Check for contamination of the PF Scale. If the PF Scale is contaminated, clean it.<br>2. Check the reading state of the PF Encoder. If reading (from the Service Program) cannot be performed, reinstall the PF Encoder.<br>3. Replace the PF Encoder.<br>4. Replace the Sub-B Board.<br>5. Replace the Main Board.'),(16,1,'SC-F6330','122C','PF Motor Reversing Error','1. PF Belt tension<br>2. PF Encoder<br>3. PF Motor','The number of occurrences of reversing the PF Motor has reached a predetermined limit.','1. Check the PF Belt state.<br>2. Check the following connections for an abnormality such as a connector disconnection or a broken cable. If an abnormality is found, reconnect it.<br>3. Replace the PF Encoder.<br>4. Replace the PF Motor.'),(17,1,'SC-F6330','122D','PF Motor Driving Time-Out Error','Main Board','Abnormally-long driving duration of the PF Motor was detected.','Replace the Main Board.'),(18,1,'SC-F6330','122E','PF Motor Velocity Deviation Error','1. PF Scale<br>2. PF Encoder<br>3. Sub-B Board<br>4. Main Board','The PF Motor was detected to be driving at an abnormal speed lower than the specified speed when driving. Or, the waveform is not detected when the PF Motor is driving.','1. Check the PF Scale state.<br>2. Check the reading state of the PF Encoder. If reading (from the Service Program) cannot be performed, replace the PF Encoder.<br>3. Replace the Sub-B Board.<br>4. Replace the Main Board.'),(19,1,'SC-F6330','122F','PF Motor Lock Error','1. PF Belt tension<br>2. PF Encoder<br>3. PF Motor','The PF Motor was detected to be driving at an abnormal speed lower than the specified speed when driving. Or, the waveform is not detected when the PF Motor is driving.','1 .Check the PF Belt state.<br>2. Check the reading state of the PF Encoder. If reading (from the Service Program) cannot be performed, replace the PF Encoder.<br>3. Replace the PF Motor.'),(20,1,'SC-F6330','131B','Head Driver (Transmission Gate) Temperature Error','1. Head FFC<br>2. Print Head<br>3. Main Board','The temperature rose and reached the specified value due to an abnormality in the Driver Circuit for head driving on the Main Board.','1. Did the product recover when the power was turned OFF/ON?<br>2. Check the Head FFC connection state. Check for an abnormality such as skewed connection. If an abnormality is found, reinstall it.<br>3. Replace the Head FFC.<br>4. Replace the Print Head.<br>5. Replace the Main Board.'),(21,1,'SC-F6330','1412','Suction Pump Life End','Pump Cap Unit','The service life of the Pump Cap Unit ended. (The Pump Motor rotation speed reached the specified value)','Replace the Pump Cap Unit (P. 269), and reset the life counter'),(22,1,'SC-F6330','1416','Pump Cap Position Unsettled Error','1. Pump Cap Unit<br>2. Main Board<br>3. Relay Cable','Pump Cap Unit failure','1. Check the following connections.<br>Check the connection between the Main Board and Pump Cap Unit (CN14) for an abnormality such as connector disconnection, abnormal noise, a broken cable, or failure of the Position Control Sensor in the Pump Cap. If an abnormality is found, reconnect it.<br>Does the product recover from the error?<br>2. Check the Pump Cap Unit operation state.<br>3. Replace the Main Board.<br>4. Due to the possibility of a broken cable, replace the relay cable.'),(23,1,'SC-F6330','1418','Pump Motor Overcurrent Error','1. Relay Connector<br>2. Pump Cap Unit<br>3. Main Board replacement<br>4. Relay Cable','The cycle of voltage to the Pump Motor is unstable and the number of overcurrent detections reached the specified value.','1. Check the Pump Cap Unit operation state.<br>2. Check the following connections for an abnormality such as a connector disconnection or a broken cable. If an abnormality is found, reconnect it.<br>3. Check the Pump Cap Unit operation state.<br>4. Replace the Main Board.<br>5. Due to the possibility of a broken cable, replace the relay cable.'),(24,1,'SC-F6330','1419','Pump Motor Oscillation Error','1. Main Board (Pump Motor Driver)<br>2. Pump Cap Unit','The number of oscillations exceeds the specified value. Or, the control terminal (Vre terminal) of the Pump Motor Driver was short-circuited.','1. Check the Main Board state.<br>2. If the product does not recover, replace the Main Board.<br>3. Check the Pump Cap Unit operation state.'),(25,1,'SC-F6330','141A','Pump Motor Overload Error','1. Relay Connector<br>2. Pump Cap Unit<br>3. Main Board replacement<br>4. Relay Cable','The Pump Motor did not operate normally due to some load and an overcurrent higher than the specified value was detected.','1. Execute power OFF/ON (the cycle may be corrected by power OFF/ON).<br>2. Check the obstacle in the Pump Cap Unit operation range.<br>3. Check the Relay Connector connection.<br>4. Check the Pump Cap Unit operation state.<br>5. Replace the Main Board.<br>6. Due to a possibility of a broken cable, replace the relay cable.'),(26,1,'SC-F6330','141B','Pump Motor Over Speed Error','1. Pump Cap Unit<br>2. Main Board','The Pump Motor was detected to be operating at a speed faster than the specified speed when decelerating.','1. Check the Pump Cap Unit operation state.<br>2. Replace the Main Board.'),(27,1,'SC-F6330','141C','Pump Motor Reversing Error','1. Pump Cap Unit<br>2. Main Board','The Pump Motor was detected to be operating at a speed faster than the specified speed when decelerating','1. Check the Pump Cap Unit operation state.<br>2. Replace the Main Board.'),(28,1,'SC-F6330','141C','Pump Motor Reversing Error','Pump Cap Unit','The number of occurrences of reversing the Pump Motor has reached a predetermined limit.','1. Check the following connections for an abnormality such as a connector disconnection or a broken cable. If an abnormality is found, reconnect it. Pump Motor (Pump Motor Encoder) to Main Board (CN14)<br>2. Check the Pump Cap Unit operation state.'),(29,1,'SC-F6330','141D','Pump Motor Driving Time-Out Error','1. Pump Cap Unit<br>2. Main Board','Abnormally-long driving duration of the Pump Motor was detected','1. Check the Pump Cap Unit operation state.<br>2. Replace the Main Board.'),(30,1,'SC-F6330','141E','Pump Motor Velocity Deviation Error','1. Pump Cap Unit<br>2. Main Board','The Pump Motor was driven at a speed abnormally faster than a predetermined one during acceleration or deceleration.','1. Check the Pump Cap Unit operation state.<br>2. Replace the Main Board.'),(31,1,'SC-F6330','141F','Pump Motor Lock Error','Pump Cap Unit','The Pump Motor was driven at a speed abnormally slower than a predetermined one during operation. Or, the w